This function uses the combination sort algorithm, which is a variation of the quicksort algorithm. The main idea is to partition the list into two sub-lists: one with elements smaller than a chosen pivot, and one with elements greater than the pivot. The function recursively sorts both sub-lists and then combines them.

The helper function, `comb_sort_helper`, takes a subset of the list and partitions it around a chosen pivot. It then recursively sorts both the left and right sub-lists and combines them with the pivot.

This implementation is correct because it sorts the list in ascending order. It has a worst-case time complexity of O(n^2), and a typical case time complexity of O(n log n). The space complexity is O(log n).

